<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU Summit Urges U.N. to Lift Sanctions on Libya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOME, July 12 (Xinhua) - The Organization of African Unity (OAU)
leaders Wednesday called on the U.N. Security Council to totally
lift the nine-year sanctions on Libya as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The leaders, at their annual summit held here in the Togolese
capital on July 10-12, also backed Libya to seek compensation for
the damages caused by the imposition of sanctions.
</P>
<P>
They expressed satisfaction at the beginning of the trial of
the two Libyan suspects in the Netherlands and requested that all
the necessary conditions are provided to ensure that the trial is
fair, neutral and transparent.
</P>
<P>
Britain and the United States pushed for an air and arms
embargo against Libya in 1992 after the country refused to hand
over two suspects accused of blowing up a PanAm airline flight 103
over Lockerbie, Scotland, in 1988, killing 230 people aboard.
</P>
</TEXT>
