<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Tries to Eradicate Tse-Tse Flies With New Technique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 13 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia is using a new
technique known as sterile insect technique to eradicate tse-tse
flies, an official of the Ethiopian Science and Technology
Commission said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The new technology refers to a way of multiplying and releasing
sterilized male tse-tse flies in areas infested with the flies to
minimize sexual intercourse among the natural flies, thus stopping
their multiplication gradually.
</P>
<P>
A South Ethiopia Rift Valley Eradication Project has been
launched to help apply the new technique, said Kahsay Wolde, chief
of the planning and program section with the commission.
</P>
<P>
According to Kahsay, anti-tse-tse chemicals have been used in
some areas in southern Ethiopia which is prone to infestation of
the flies, but no desired results were achieved.
</P>
<P>
Tse-tse flies cause many diseases, one of which is known as
rinderpest that is infectious among people, the official said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
