<HEADLINE> Canada Donates 2 Million U.S. Dollars to Tanzania Over Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 13 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian government has
donated 1.6 billion Tanzanian shillings (about 2 million U.S.
dollars) to help implement a basic education project in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The donation, announced Thursday by Canadian Minister for
International Cooperation Maria Anna, is granted through the
Canadian International Development Agency, according to a
statement released by the Canadian High Commission in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The donation is aimed at supporting the Tanzanian government in
its efforts to develop basic education programs and to improve
school administration in disadvantaged districts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The three-year project will also help Tanzania's education
system to better meet the needs of children both within and
outside the formal school system by focusing on gender equality,
HIV/AIDS prevention and environmental education.
</P>
<P>
Anna arrived here on Wednesday for a three-day visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
