<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- Oman's accession to the World Trade Organization
(WTO) could have been speeded up had some key legislations not
taken more time, said a senior official of the world body.
</P>
<P>
There was also lack of expertise on some subjects such as
customs evaluation, the Dubai-based Gulf News daily Friday quoted
Cato Adrian, WTO's counsellor in the accession division, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Asked if Oman has met all of the WTO requirements, Adrian said
over the phone from Geneva that a patent law has yet to be enacted
along with some legislations concerning intellectual property.
(BC-Oman-WTO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- The Turkish Navy will grant a TCG AB 34-type fighter
boat to the Azerbaijani Naval Forces in line with a military
cooperation pact between the two countries, said a statement issued
Friday by the Turkish Naval Forces Command.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony will be held on July 17 to mark the delivery at
Emircakabey Quay of Izmir, southwest Turkey, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
After the ceremony, the boat will set sail for Azerbaijan with
28 Azerbaijani naval personnel and two Turkish advisors on board.
(BC-Turkey-Azerbaijan-Fighter Boat)
</P>
<P>
