<HEADLINE> U.S. Industrial Production Up 0.2 Percent in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Industrial production at U.S.
factories, mines and utilities increased 0.2 percent in June, the
slowest pace since September, the Federal Reserve reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
In May, industrial production posted a 0.5 percent gain.
</P>
<P>
On a year-on-year basis, industrial production in June was up 5.
8 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the second quarter, industrial output advanced at a
seven percent annual rate, up from a 6.5 percent pace in the first
quarter.
</P>
<P>
Auto production rose 1.7 percent in June after a 0.7 percent
decline in May.
</P>
<P>
U.S. industry operated at 82.1 percent of capacity in June,
down from 82.2 percent the month before. 
