<HEADLINE> Xinhua Summary of Asia-Pacific Stocks News, Friday, July 14 Xinhua Summary Asia-Pacific Stocks News Friday, July 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI -- The Composite Stock Index on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange finished at 1,987.19 points Friday, up 7.99 points from
the previous session, according to the Guangfa Securities Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
SHENZHEN -- The Component Stock Index on the Shenzhen Stock
Exchange closed at 4,834.61 points Friday, down 4.51 points from
the previous session, according to the Guangfa Securities Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
HONG KONG -- Hong Kong stocks rose 59.12 points, or 0.34
percent, to open at 17,508.62 Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks rose 38.18 points, or 0.22 percent, to finish
Friday's morning session at 17,487.68.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the
First Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange rose 106.00 points, or 0.
62 percent, from Thursday's close to end at 17,142.90 after losing
more than 530 points over the previous three days.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, gained 5.70 points or 0.36 percent to 1,579.
86.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- Share prices in the Philippine Stock Exchange fell
Friday amid absence of market-moving news to spur market activity.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, fell 7.63
points to close at 1553.89. The broader all shares index, however,
marginally rose 0.33 of a point to 667.02.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thai shares slipped again Friday, hurt by recent
weakening of the baht.
</P>
<P>
The bench mark composite Stock Exchange of Thailand (SET) index
fell 4.87 points, or 1.51 percent, to close at 315.58 points.
</P>
<P>
The blue-chip SET 50 index ended down 0.41 point, or 1.8
percent, at 22.35.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR-- Share prices on the Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange
closed lower Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index lost 4.53
points to 856.24, the all-share Emas Index fell 1.64 points to 215.
74, the Industrial Index dropped 6.24 points to 1,488.30 and the
Second board Index dipped 4.25 points to 231.20.
</P>
