<HEADLINE> Loosening of Foreign Exchange Refuted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The State Administration of
Foreign Exchange (SAFE) said today it is a rumor that the State
has loosened the limits of trading RMB with foreign currencies by
students going abroad for further studies.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the SAFE reiterated that each student who wants
to study abroad for a bachelor's degree or above can exchange 2,
000 U.S. dollars or the equivalent amount of other foreign
currencies, at a designated bank with a visa issued by the
designated country.
</P>
<P>
If the student needs more than 2,000 U.S. dollars of foreign
currency, he or she should present a special application to a
local branch of the SAFE; and if the demand exceeds 50,000 U.S.
dollars, the student should apply to the head office of the SAFE,
the spokesman said.  
</P>
