<HEADLINE> Belarus Looking Forward to Chinese Vice-President Hu's Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Belarus is looking forward to
Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao's visit later this month, said a
Belarus diplomat today.
</P>
<P>
Krylov Petrovich, charge d'affaires ad interim of the Belarus
embassy in Beijing, told Xinhua that during the visit, leaders of
the two countries are expected to discuss bilateral relations and
the international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
He said the agreements to be signed during the trip are sure to
broaden prospects for bilateral cooperation in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He said China-Belarus relations, based on friendship, equality
and mutual benefit, have gone well since the forging of diplomatic
relations in 1992.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries share similar viewpoints and support
each other on many international issues.
</P>
<P>
Belarus and China have found common ground in opposition to the
U.S. Theater Missile Defense (TMD) system, he pointed out, saying
that both believe the system will threaten stability in Europe and
the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
He also praised China's important role in the international
arena.
</P>
<P>
Petrovich said frequent exchanges of visits between leaders of
the two countries play an important role in promoting cooperation
and friendship between the two sides, noting the fact that two-way
trade has increased by 400 percent over the past five years, and
the two countries have had fruitful cooperation in scientific
research, electronics, machinery and chemistry.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the two countries have launched more than 40 projects
in recent years, he added.
</P>
<P>
"A lot of work remains to be done to further expand economic
and trade cooperation," he said, adding that Belarus hopes to
promote cooperation with China in high-tech, education and culture.
</P>
<P>
China's strategy to develop its western region will provide
fresh opportunities for expanding bilateral economic cooperation,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Belarus is prepared to participate in water conservancy,
highway construction and environment protection in China's west by
giving full play to its technological and intelligence advantages,
he added. 
</P>
