<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Foreign Exchange Reserves Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Central Bank said
Friday that gross official reserves held by the government and
central bank stood at 1.386 billion U.S. dollars at the end of May,
down 15.4 percent from 1.639 billion dollars at the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The bank said in a statement the country's total reserves, or
official assets plus funds held by commercial banks, totaled 2.352
billion U.S. dollars at the end of May, a decrease of 8.9 percent
over the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Last month the bank unexpectedly depreciated the country's
currency rupee in a bid to boost the flagging exports and increase
foreign exchange reserves.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's trade deficit in the first four months of 2000 was
746.5 million dollars against 410.1 million dollars in the same
period last year. 
</P>
