<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The sixth multinational peacekeeping
exercise "Peace Shield-2000" officially began at Ukraine's Yavoriv
training range Friday, the Interfax-Ukraine news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Around 1,600 servicemen from 21 countries -- Azerbaijan,
Bulgaria, Belarus, Georgia, Kazakhstan, Ukraine, Moldova, Estonia,
Greece, Denmark, Italy, Spain, Canada, Germany, Norway, Poland,
the U.S., Turkey, Finland, Sweden and the UK -- are taking part in
the exercise, which will last until July 22.
