<HEADLINE> Turkey to Grant Fighter Boat to Azerbaijan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish Navy will grant a TCG AB
34-type fighter boat to the Azerbaijani Naval Forces in line with a
military cooperation pact between the two countries, said a
statement issued Friday by the Turkish Naval Forces Command.
</P>
<P>
A ceremony will be held on July 17 to mark the delivery at
Emircakabey Quay of Izmir, southwest Turkey, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
After the ceremony, the boat will set sail for Azerbaijan with
28 Azerbaijani naval personnel and two Turkish advisors on board.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has attached great importance to the development of
political, economic and military relations with Azerbaijan since
the disintegration of the Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Azerbaijani capital of Baku, first official
trip abroad since his assumption in office on May 16, President
Ahmet Necdet Sezer pledged on Wednesday that Turkey, a NATO member,
backed
Azerbaijan's closer integration with international organizations.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Turkey recently launched a diplomatic
offensive in the Caucasus region in an effort to counter the
increasing influence of Russia in the former Soviet republics.
</P>
</TEXT>
