<HEADLINE> Malaysia, France to Enhance Military Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and France are to
forge stronger bilateral military ties especially in personnel
training, Malaysian Chief of Defense Forces Gen. Mohamed Zahidi
Zainuddin said Friday.
</P>
<P>
This would entail, among other things, exchange and secondment
of each other's military officers, Zahidi said.
</P>
<P>
"Enhancing long-established ties will also be done through
exchange of personnel through courses," he told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Gen. Zahidi was Friday bestowed with France's second highest
award the "French National Order of Merit" in recognition of his
role in strengthening Malysia-France military ties.
</P>
<P>
He received the award from French ambassador to Malaysia Xavier
Dr'iencourt on-board the French naval vessel "FNS Aconit" docking
at the South Port of Port Klang near here.
</P>
<P>
The general said "I regard this award as one dedicated to all
members of the armed forces at all levels who in their own way
contributed towards improving ties between the armed forces of the
two countries."
</P>
<P>
The Lafayette-class French frigate manned by a complement of
153 officers and men is on a four-day visit to Malaysia from
Thursday.
</P>
</TEXT>
