<HEADLINE> Nigeria Not to Compromise Its Unity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo
has assured his fellow Nigerians that his democratically-elected
government will not compromise the unity of the country under
whatever guise, said a source here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In an address at the swearing-in ceremony of the new corps
members in the capital Abuja, Obasanjo said whatever religious,
ethnic, economic or ideological differences Nigerians had should
be settled peacefully.
</P>
<P>
Obasanjo, who was represented by the Minister of the Federal
Capital Territory, Alhaji Ibrahim Bunu, stressed that the only
national basis for dialog among Nigerians was for all to start
believing in the unity of the country.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria was facing serious problems, such as unemployment and
poverty, said the president, adding that a national approach
should be adopted to deal with the challenging problems for the
development of the country.
</P>
<P>
He also charged Nigerians to be committed and be prepared to
make sacrifices as the country launched various programs to solve
the problems afflicting the society. 
</P>
</TEXT>
