<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) has provided a
credit line of 900 million yuan (about 108 million U.S. dollars)
to Sony Corp's seven subsidiaries in China.
</P>
<P>
The branch signed an agreement with Sony Thursday in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The credit line will meet the growing demands of the companies
for working capital.
</P>
<P>
