<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices in Hong Kong closed
higher on Friday, propped up by resurgent international
conglomerate Hutchison Whampoa and a few other blue chips as the
rest of the market consolidated after recent heavy gains.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index closed 0.78 percent, or 136.66
points, higher at 17,586.16.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on Friday was 12.748 billion HK dollars (1.634 billion
U.S. dollars), compared to Thursday's 18.751 billion HK dollars (2.
404 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices, Finance lost 0.53 percent, while
Utilities, Properties and Industry &AMP; Commerce went up by 0.31
percent, 1.31 percent and 1.33 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index gained 3.68 percent,
while the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corp Index lost 0.86 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index went up 0.36 percent while the Hang Seng
IT Portfolio Index dropped by 0.95 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the first three days of the week, the Hang Seng Index gained
a total of 722 points, from 16,829.96 last Friday to 17,552.26 on
Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
