<HEADLINE> China and Laos to Promote Relations (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- China and Laos will promote their
cooperative relations in the years to come, according to today's
talks between the presidents of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said relations between the two
countries and parties have been developing well since the
normalization of bilateral relations 10 years ago and have yielded
positive results, and peace and stability in border area have
maintained.
</P>
<P>
He told visiting Lao President Khamtay Siphandone: "We are
satisfied with the smooth development of bilateral relations."
</P>
<P>
Khamtay Siphandone, who arrived here Thursday on a three-day
state visit, said his visit will play an important role in
promoting the further development of a time-honored friendship and
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the good development of bilateral relations is
ensured by leaders of the two countries who have always attached
importance to bilateral relations and their frequent exchanges of
visits.
</P>
<P>
He said the two sides share common ideal and belief, persist in
taking the socialist road under the leadership of their ruling
parties, pursue the policy of reform and opening-up, and have the
same or identical viewpoints on many important international and
regional issues.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the two parties and peoples have supported the
development of Sino-Lao friendly relations no matter in the
revolutionary struggle or peaceful time, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He said these are favorable conditions and important basis for
promoting all-round cooperation between the two countries in the
years ahead.
</P>
<P>
Khamtay Siphandone said the Lao People's Revolutionary Party (
LPRP) and government are satisfied with bilateral relations and
the further development of a long-term and stable relationship
between the two countries in the new century conforms to the
fundamental interests of their peoples.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000714.0133 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China and Laos to Promote Relations (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He also congratulated China for the smooth return of Hong Kong
and Macao due to the successful implementation of the policy of "
one country, two systems" initiated by Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the Lao government believes Taiwan is an
inseparable part of the Chinese territory, saying Laos will
continue to support China's reunification and pursue the one-China
policy.
</P>
<P>
Khamtay briefed Jiang on Lao domestic situation. He said in
recent years, Laos has stuck to the leadership of the LPRP and an
all-round and principled guideline of innovation.
</P>
<P>
Despite the Asian financial crisis, Laos, through its efforts,
has maintained social stability and economic development, and
scored achievements in both internal and external affairs, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said all the facts prove that the LPRP is powerful and
cohesive, and will lead the Lao people to overcome difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders reached common ground on furthering
comprehensive and cooperative relations between the two countries,
and will as soon as possible sign a document to define the
framework for the further development of Sino-Lao relations.
</P>
<P>
Khamtay once again invited Jiang to visit Laos. Jiang accepted
the invitation.  
</P>
