<HEADLINE> Share Prices Slide on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) eased by 5.12 points to
2,079.89 points at close bouncing back from the intraday low of 2,
069.75 points in moderate trading.
</P>
<P>
The total volume contracted to 534.25 million units valued at
591.03 million Singapore dollars (339.19 million U.S. dollars).
There were 118 gainers against 194 losers with 239 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
North22, a newly-listed stock, topped the volume list as it
registered a turnover of 119.77 million units. Achieva was the
second most heavily traded stock with 35.81 million shares done.
Brierley was the next with 27.10 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
PacCent was the biggest gainer of the day surging up 110 cents
to close at 24.90 Singapore dollars. It was followed by Venture
which rose by 50 cents to 20.00 Singapore dollars at finish.
Chartered and NatElec picked up 40 cents to end at 15.20 and 5.60
Singapore dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
OCBC led losers of the day giving up 40 cents to end at 12.10
Singapore dollars. Seaview retreated 35 cents to finish at 7.75
Singapore dollars. Creative 50 and DBS shed 20 cents to end at 37.
90 and 22.00 Singapore dollars, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted that technology stocks enjoyed a very buoyant
session Friday cheered by 1.8 percent climb in the U.S. NASDAQ.
</P>
</TEXT>
