<HEADLINE> China to Dispatch New Medical Team to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- China will send a new medical
team, the 11th of its kind since 1980, to render its services in
Ethiopia on the eve of the 30th anniversary of establishment of
diplomatic ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador Jiang Zhengyun and Ethiopian Vice Minister
of Economic Development and Cooperation Mulatu Teshome signed an
agreement to the effect on behalf of their respective governments
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The practice of dispatching medical team has turned out to be
one of helpful and effective ways of cooperation in the field of
health between China and African countries, including Ethiopia,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The 15-member Chinese medical team, due to arrive here in
August, is expected to provide its services in Nazareth, about 100
kilometers south of Addis Ababa, and a dental center affiliated to
Addis Ababa University.
</P>
<P>
China and Ethiopia established diplomatic ties on November 24,
1970. 
