<DOCNO> XIE20000714.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nanjing City Enjoying Cool Summer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- While the Chinese capital of
Beijing is heating under the scorching sun, Nanjing, known as one
of China's four "heating ovens", is enjoying a cool summer with
the average maximum temperature reading 30 degrees Celsius.
</P>
<P>
Major cities in north and east China have had their maximum
temperatures shooting up to over 32 degrees Celsius. Beijing's
highest temperature soared up to over 40 degrees Celsius.
</P>
<P>
However, this capital of east China's Jiangsu Province has
become a summer resort with pretty cool weather.
</P>
<P>
There are four "ovens" in the Yangtze River valleys: Nanjing,
Jiujiang, Wuhan and Chongqing cities. Temperatures in the four
cities are usually higher in summer than in other places on the
same latitude, because of radiative effects of the river water.
</P>
<P>
The abnormal atmospheric circulation and expanded urban
greenery have been attributed to the low summer temperature.
Nanjing's per-capita greenery coverage amounts to 7 sq.m., which
represents a high greenery rate among the cities along the Yangtze
River.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing was struck by a heat wave in 1998, when a 38-40-degree
Celsius temperature lingered for weeks in summer. However, the
city's highest temperature dropped below 35 degrees Celsius in
July last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000714.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Precious Ancient Coins Unearthed in North China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archaeologists
recently unearthed precious ancient coins in north China's Hebei
province.
</P>
<P>
Among the discovery, 42 coins were made in the Northern Song
Dynasty (960-1127) and some words were engraved on them, which are
believed to be written by the emperors at that time.
</P>
<P>
To engrave some lucky words on coins is common in ancient China,
but such kinds of coins with emperors' handwritings are rare in
the region, said experts.
</P>
<P>
The coins along with other relics were found in tombs located
about 20 km southeast to Shenzhou city, in the southeastern part
of Hebei province.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists recently discovered about 11 tombs presumably
built in the Tang Dynasty (618-907) and Song Dynasty (960-1279)
near an express way in the province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000714.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China: Top of the Week (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The following are the major
domestic news Xinhua released from July 8 to 14:
</P>
<P>
-- China's industrial enterprises are expected to achieve a net
profit of 300 billion yuan (36.1 billion U.S. dollars) in 2000.
The state-owned and state-controlled companies are expected to
generate 130 billion yuan (15.7 billion U.S. dollars) in profits,
according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
-- More than 10,000 people had been evacuated to safe places by
July 9 morning in southwest China's Chongqing Metropolis after
their houses were threatened by mountain slides caused by days of
torrential rains.
</P>
<P>
Six days of torrential rains starting from June 1 caused eight
major mountain slides and 2,600 minor ones in the county near the
Three Gorges Reservoir area now under construction.
</P>
<P>
-- Twice a day, over 700,000 trained chickens and ducks chow
down on locusts at the foot of Tianshan Mountain in the Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region, northwest China.
</P>
<P>
Locusts have affected 2.6 million hectares of farmland in the
northwest China region. To fight back, the region has brought in
some 100,000 ducks to join the locust-killing bio-troops made up
of chickens, migrating starlings and microspores.
</P>
<P>
The disaster has now been brought under control, said officials
with the Ministry of Agriculture. But it is still too early to be
too optimistic, since combating autumn locusts could be an even
tougher task as many insects could survive the summer's
eradication program, and foreign locusts may invade at any time,
warned the officials.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000714.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China: Top of the Week (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- The tropical storm Kai-Tak landed on the coastal Yuhuan
county of east China's Zhejiang Province, 250 km from the
provincial capital of Hangzhou. But no casualty was reported.
</P>
<P>
-- China's industrial output grew by 11.2 percent over the same
period of last year in the first half of this year, registering
the highest half-year growth rate in the past three years.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the National Bureau of Statistics showed
that industrial added-value totaled 1.0996 trillion yuan (132.5
billion US dollars) during January to June.
</P>
<P>
-- The State Family Planning Commission held a meeting here on
July 10 to mark this year's World Population Day, which has the
theme of "saving women's lives".
</P>
<P>
-- The speeding up of economic globalization and the rapid
development of the high-tech industry have had a profound impact
on the political economic and social sectors of all nations, and
pose challenges to all governments, said Chinese State Councilor
Wang Zhongyu at the annual conference of the International
Association of Schools and Institutes of Administration. The State
Councilor and President of the China National School of
Administration said a government has to respond to the needs of
its people if it wants its society and economy to grow.
</P>
<P>
-- China will convert over 100 large state-run scientific
research institutes attached to State Council ministries into
ventures by the end of this year, as a major step in the reform of
the research bodies.
</P>
<P>
A total of 242 of the state-run research organs were turned
into or merged with other ventures last year.
</P>
<P>
-- China's first robot development and production company, the
Siasun Robot &AMP; Automation Co. Ltd., has been set up in Shenyang,
capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province. The establishment
of the company signifies the start of market-oriented industrial
robot production in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
