<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-share Market Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen composite index rose
1.83 points or 0.30 percent to close at 615.14 points on Thursday,
a record high for the fourth straight day.
</P>
<P>
The sub-index, however, dropped 4.52 points or 0.09 percent to
close the day at 4834.61 points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 14.08 billion yuan, 25.1 percent less than
Thursday's 18.82 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen composite index opened high today, but also
plunged to 611.19 points on profit-taking. Nevertheless, market
sentiment remained bullish and investors turned their interest to
the oil-related stocks after learning about price hikes for
gasoline and diesel, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Market gainers beat losers by 248 to 222, with another nine
stocks unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Chengdu Shudu Mansion Co. Ltd was the top gainer today. Its
price soared 9.97 percent to close at 13.01 yuan per share
</P>
<P>
Wanxiang Qianchao Co. Ltd was the biggest loser, with price
dropping 6.77 percent to close at 14.88 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Analysts note that the market is likely to try a new high next
week, but profit-taking pressure is also very high after one-week
strong rally and technical adjustments are inevitable.  
</P>
</TEXT>
