<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market in Correction on Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- China's securities investment fund
market was mainly in a correction on Friday, according to Homeway,
a leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Of the 27 funds, 12 rose, 8 dropped and 7 remained unchanged.
24 funds fluctuated within the range of 1 percent. The other three
restructured funds, however, changed more than 1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Fund Tongzhi continued to rise, up 4.19 percent at the market
close, while Fund Yuhua and Fund Zhujiang fell by 1.6 percent and
1.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Fund market on the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock exchange
basically kept a steady rising trend.
</P>
<P>
The fund index on the Shanghai Stock Exchange closed at 1022.12
points, up 0.63 percent compared with last week's close at 1015.73
points.
</P>
<P>
The fund index on the Shenzhen Stock Exchange closed at 1036.92
points, up 1.45 percent compared to the last week's close at 1022.
14 points.  
