<HEADLINE> Shanghai A-share Market Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai composite index
closed at 1987.19 points on Friday, up 7.99 points or 0.40 percent
compared with the last close.
</P>
<P>
Total trading volume was 16.36 billion yuan, 15.4 percent less
than the previous session's 19.35 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
This is the sixth consecutive day when the market index
finished at a new record high. The market opened high in the
morning but plunged soon to 1973.09 points on profit-taking,
according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, the market sentiment remained bullish and
investors turned their interest to the oil-related stocks such as
chemical firms after learning the news of oil price hikes.
Starting from today, the prices of gasoline and diesel oil were up
by seven percent or 200 yuan and 180 yuan respectively.
</P>
<P>
The index then began to climb up, fluctuated all day and
finally closed at 1987.19 points.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1.3 billion shares changed hands today.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Petrochemical Co., Ltd and Beijing Wangfujing
Department Store (Group) Co., Ltd were the top gainers today, with
the prices of both shares soaring 9.96 percent. The former closed
at 5.52 yuan per share and the latter at 10.05 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang Friendship (Group) Co., Ltd was the biggest loser. Its
price, which had soared considerably over the past three days,
shed 7.98 percent to finish at 16.83 yuan per share on profit
taking.
</P>
<P>
The market is likely to try a new high next week. However,
analysts say that the profit-taking pressure is also very high
after one-week strong ally, and technical adjustments are
inevitable.  
</P>
</TEXT>
