<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-share Market Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share market index
edged up 0.11 points, or 0.19 percent to 57.35 on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 13.32 million US dollars, 27.13 percent less than
Thursday's total.
</P>
<P>
The market slipped off its highs, but the losses were
relatively minor with the market tone weakening just slightly as
the session progressed. Generally speaking, it was still holding a
bullish bias as favorable economic fundamentals continued to
underpin, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial
and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
China's economy rose at a rate of 8.2 percent in the first half
of this year, and the slowdown caused partly by the Asian
financial crisis is expected to come to an end later this year.
</P>
<P>
However, the market had for a while been hampered by the swirl
of speculation surrounding the half-year revenue figures.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outpaced declining shares by 24 to 19, with 11
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that range trading has dominated in the modest
advance but it is attempting to trek higher next week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
