<HEADLINE> Manila Stocks End Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices in the Philippine
Stock Exchange fell Friday amid absence of market-moving news to
spur market activity.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, fell 7.63
points to close at 1553.89. The broader all shares index, however,
marginally rose 0.33 of a point to 667.02.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 608 million shares worth some 16 million U.S.
dollars on Friday against Thursday's 1.09 billion shares worth
some 33 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said investors stayed at the sideways due to lack of
investment perks to spur market activity. They said investors also
remained wary over the peso-dollar movement.
</P>
<P>
Dominant telephone company Philippine Long Distance Telephone
Company was the most actively traded issue, but it remained
unchanged at 770 pesos (19.25 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On Friday's trading, losers outpaced gainers, 47 to 23, with 60
unchanged issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
