Friday morning off the waters of Bantayan island in Cebu province
of the central Philippines, according to a TV report.
</P>
<P>
The ABS-CBN television said the vessel, Don Martin Senior,
became partially submerged after huge waves brought by bad weather
entered its engine room.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-seven passengers ad crew members of the vessel were
rescued by three nearby sea crafts responding to the distress call
made by the ill-fated ship at about 5:05 a.m. Friday.
</P>
<P>
Five people have been reported missing, including a five-year-
old boy. The boy, identified as John David Martinez, allegedly
slipped from his mother's grasp when the boat began to tilt to its
side.
</P>
<P>
While the total number of persons rescued tallied 77, the ship'
s owners said there were only 72 people listed on the ship's
manifesto.
</P>
<P>
The MBO Palacio Shipping Lines, the vessel's owner, declared
that there were 39 passengers and 33 crew members on board the
vessel.
</P>
<P>
So far, search-and-rescue operations are underway to locate the
missing passengers, said the TV report. 
</P>
