1998, while wheat imports dropped from 2.538 billion pounds (731.4
million dollars)in 1998 to 1.933 billion pounds (557.06 million
dollars)last year. Wheat self-sufficiency rose from 25 percent in
1982 to 55 percent last year, according to a recent report by the
Central Agency for Mobilization of Cotton.
</P>
<P>
Al Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- EgyptAir on Thursday resumed its regular flights to Libya
after an eight-year hiatus forced by the U.N. sanctions imposed
against Libya since April 1992. The first flight landed earlier in
the day at Tripoli Airport, carrying on board a high-level Egyptian
delegation.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- A 10-day heat wave in Egypt, that scorched the whole nation,
will come to an end Friday, said a senior meteorology official
Thursday. Temperatures will drop soon to 34-35 degrees Celsius in
Cairo and lower Egypt, 28 degrees Celsius in northern coastal areas
and to 38 degrees Celsius in southern Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
