<HEADLINE> ASEAN Meeting to Include Exhibition on Regional Heritages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 14 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition on cultural
heritages of member states of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) will be organized here in conjunction with the
33rd ASEAN Ministerial Meeting (AMM) later this month, the Thai
News Agency (TAN) reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Secretary-General of the Office of the National Culture
Commission Arthorn Chanthawomol was quoted as saying that the
ASEAN Cultural Heritage Exhibition would also be held at the
Shangri-La Hotel here, the venue of the AMM.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministers of 10 ASEAN member states would also sign an
ASEAN Declaration on Cultural heritages at the AMM, held between
July 24 and 29, he said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will feature five main themes, including pottery,
textile, musical instruments, archeological sites, and ornaments,
with photographs, documents, and samples of cultural objects from
all the ASEAN member countries.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now groups Brunei, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia,
Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition would be jointly organized by the Office of the
National Culture Commission and its counterparts in the ASEAN
Committee on Culture and Information (ASEAN COCI), and the Public
Relation Department of Thailand, said Arthorn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
