<HEADLINE> Baht Rates Acceptable: BOT Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The current rates of the Thai baht
are still at an acceptable level and favorable to the country's
exports, the Thai News Agency (TNA) reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Governor of the Bank of Thailand (BOT) Chutamongkol Sonakul was
quoted as saying on Thursday that the baht fluctuation, between 39
baht and just over 40 baht for a U.S. dollar, during the past few
days was gradual and within the market mechanism.
</P>
<P>
The fall, though being a nine-month low, was rational and
within trading range, when compared to other currencies in the
region which also experienced weakening rates, he said.
</P>
<P>
It would also benefit the country's export sector, and would be
unlikely to cause investment outflow or affect the repayment
ability of the private sector, he projected.
</P>
<P>
The BOT would continue its low interest policy because it is
crucial to the recovering process of the Thai economy, said the
central bank governor. 
</P>
