<HEADLINE> Construction of China's North-South Expressway Gets Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the southern
section of a national north-south expressway has got a boost with
a leading Chinese bank promising to provide loans to support the
project.
</P>
<P>
The Construction Bank of China signed an agreement Thursday
with the Guangshao Expressway Co., Ltd., a company based in south
China's Guangdong Province responsible for the construction, on
extending a 10-year loan totaling 3.07 billion yuan (369 million U.
S. dollars) for the project.
</P>
<P>
The southern section of the expressway linking Beijing to
Zhuhai City in Guangdong, neighboring Macao, is 198.8 kilometers
long and will cost 8.6 billion yuan. Construction began in late
1998 and is planned for completion at the end of 2002.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Guangzhou-Zhuhai expressway, a key state project,
will be the only one of its kind connecting Beijing with the Macao
Special Administrative Region. The Guangzhou-Zhuhai section was
completed and open to traffic before the return of Macao to China
in December 1999.  
</P>
</TEXT>
