<DOCNO> XIE20000714.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tornado Kills 10 and Injures 500 in East China (Recast) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A tornado in east China's Jiangsu
Province has left 10 people dead and 500 others injured.
</P>
<P>
The tornado hit Yangzhou and Taizhou cities in the province at
about 3:40 p.m. Thursday, destroying more than 4,000 houses and
uprooting big trees.
</P>
<P>
The natural disaster also suspended power supplies, cut off
telecommunications and disrupted TV and radio signals. Workers are
working hard to restore damaged facilities.
</P>
<P>
The tornado has affected more than 20,000 hectares of paddy
fields and 5,300 hectares of cotton farms, causing more than 4
million yuan (about 480,000 U.S. dollars) of losses to agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Rescuers have arrived in the affected areas and the local
government has made arrangements to ensure the victims have food,
shelter and medical care.  
</P>
</TEXT>
