<HEADLINE> Seniloli Appointed Fiji's Vice President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Fiji's Great Council of Chiefs
Friday appointed Jope Seniloli the country's new vice president,
the fijilive.com website said.
</P>
<P>
Seniloli's name for vice president was put in by coup leader
George Speight and endorsed at a meeting of district chiefs
convened last Wednesday, the website said.
</P>
<P>
The chiefs resolved that all road blocks around Fiji should be
lifted.
</P>
<P>
Also on Friday, decrees giving Speight and his coup members as
well as supporters amnesty and specifying transfer of executive
authority from military commander Commodore Frank Bainimarama to
the new president, Josefa Iloilo, had been gazetted, the website
said.
</P>
<P>
The website quoted military spokesman Howard Politini as saying
that arrangements have been made with Speight's group to return
all arms and ammunition in their possession to the military armory
Friday afternoon. 
