<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese legendary Woman Becomes Disney Heroine (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mulan was eulogized throughout the centuries in China as a
personalized woman for her devotion to the country. And some
Disney producers have also added much ode to her, saying that
Mulan represents the trend of women's liberation and displays the
equality between men and women since she did better than man in a
period when women were always at a subordinate position.
</P>
<P>
However, compared with the brilliance of her popularity, the
temple to Mulan in the village seems somewhat desolate and the
traces of just a few visitors can be seen in the ruderal temple
compound.
</P>
<P>
"Very few people know the hometown of Mulan, despite her story
spreads far and wide, said Ma Jizhong, a local publicity official.
</P>
<P>
The local government held a "Mulan Cultural Festival" in the
village last May, which, to the surprise of local people,
attracted more than 100,000 visitors, many of them came from other
provinces, said Ma, adding that local travel agencies are working
out a new tourist route related to Mulan's hometown.
</P>
<P>
"Mulan Temple is indeed an ideal tourism destination in the
locality, I believe Mulan's hometown will soon become a world
attraction," he said.
</P>
<P>
The promotion of the images of Mulan and the Mulan Temple will
be conducive to educating the public in the status and role of
women in modern China. However, to achieve real equality between
men and women needs a long way to go, and the Mulan Temple might
contribute a bit to that. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000714.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Legendary Women Becomes Disney Heroine (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGQIU,(Henan Province) July 14 (Xinhua) -- This is a middle-
sized normal village encircled by lush growing trees and bushes,
but here rest at peace a legendary women warrior who is also a
heroine of one of Disney's most successful animated features.
</P>
<P>
The village is the hometown of Hua Mulan-- whose real surname
was Wei -- a young girl believed to be born about 1,300 years ago
in what today is called Dazhou Village in eastern Henan province's
Yucheng county. Her tomb can still be found here.
</P>
<P>
According to both historic records and the folk story, the
delicate young woman disguises herself as a young man to serve in
the army to keep her aging father from having to fight in the
battle field. During the 12-year war with the invading northern
tribes, she carefully hides her true identity and was finally
awarded by the emperor for outstanding military exploits.
</P>
<P>
A memorial temple for Mulan, first erected during the Tang
Dynasty (618-907) and rebuilt in 1994, is now the highest and most
significant building in the village, inside which a two-meter tall
woodcarving figure of Mulan always reminds local people and
visitors of her patriotism and courage.
</P>
<P>
The Disney cartoon "Mulan", based on this Chinese folk story,
has been translated into six languages and attracted worldwide
attention, making Mulan one of the most famous world figures like
Cinderella and Aladdin.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000714.0232 </DOCNO>
