<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Revenue Earnings Fail to Achieve Targets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Revenue earnings have
failed to achieve the original and revised targets for the fiscal
1999-2000 despite heavy reducing of the fiscal's target, according
to statistics released by the National Board of Revenue (NBR) here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The collection of tax revenue through NBR during the just-
concluded fiscal amounted to 3.01 billion U.S. dollars as against
the original target of 3.5 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The collection of revenue has also failed to achieve the
revised target of 3.2 billion dollars fixed for the year 1999-2000
just a few months ago.
</P>
<P>
The figure is, however, 38 million dollars, or 1.28 percent
higher than the amount earned during the same period in the
previous fiscal (1998-1999).
</P>
<P>
The falling industrial performance, port congestion, drop in
imports with high import duties, large-scale smuggling of foreign
goods and fixation of very ambitious targets reportedly were the
main reasons for the decline in revenue collection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
