<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, July 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The United States and Vietnam on Thursday signed
a historic trade agreement, President Bill Clinton announced at
the White House.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Vietnam would reduce its tariffs and
undertake a series of measures to open its markets to U.S. goods,
services and investment. In return, Vietnam would get access to
the U.S. market under the same system of low tariffs accorded most
nations. (US-Vietnam-Agreement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
