MOSCOW -- Russia is trying to create conditions favoring
expansion of industry and the entire economy rather than winning
short-term popular support, President Vladimir Putin said in an
interview to be published in the Friday edition of the Izvestia
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The state has been honoring all its social commitments, making
use of the favorable situation on the world markets, but will not
expand its social programs without proper consideration, he said.
(Russia-Putin-Economy)
</P>
