- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. telecom giants WorldCom and Sprint announced
Thursday they were scrapping their merger plans, citing opposition
from U.S. and European antitrust authorities. In a statement, the
companies said that "the set of conditions ultimately demanded by
the U.S. Department of Justice would compromise the customer and
financial benefits of the merger." (US-Merger)
