<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Telecom to Provide 100,000 More Connections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka Telecom (SLT) said
Friday it plans to install another 100,000 telephones by the end
of this year.
</P>
<P>
SLT said in a statement that it had installed an underground
fiber optic cable connecting the exchanges of 15 major cities in
four provinces at a cost of 1.5 billion rupees (18.8 million U.S.
dollars) covering about 700 kilometers for faster and better
transmission.
</P>
<P>
Four more fiber optic rings are to be laid in Metro Colombo and
the suburbs connecting 27 exchanges at a cost of 400 million
rupees (5 million dollars), said the statement.
</P>
<P>
During the past four years SLT has provided 350,000 new
telephone connections.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has 283 exchanges and operates 186 transmission
towers islandwide. About 600,000 sites can now access Internet and
use the network to pursue e-commerce.
</P>
<P>
To ensure high quality international voice calls SLT has
invested in an under sea cable connecting 30 countries.
</P>
<P>
During the past three years a total of 500 million dollars has
been spent on improving infrastructure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
