<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes Over 4 Million Stimulant Drug Tablets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar Police Force seized 4.
486 million tablets of stimulant drugs at the end of last month in
Nawnghkio, a place in the country's northeastern Shan state,
official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure was jointly made by the local intelligence unit and
the police force when they searched a car in the township on June
30.
</P>
<P>
Five traffickers were arrested in connection with the case and
punishment was given to them by the authorities under the country'
s Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Law, the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, in 1999 the Myanmar
authorities seized 1,447.55 kilos of opium, 272.94 kilos of heroin,
274.48 kilos of marijuana, 278.97 liters of phensedyl, 262,542.5
liters of precursor chemicals as well as 28.75 million tablets of
stimulant drugs, destroying 12 heroin refineries. 
</P>
