<HEADLINE> Murderers of German Family Sentenced to Death (Details Added) EDS-Details Added </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Intermediate People's Court in
Nanjing City, the capital of east China's Jiangsu Province, today
granted death penalty to all four jobless youths who are convicted
of murdering and robbing a German family of four.
</P>
<P>
The four accused are Zhong Weiyang, 20; Liu Guangyuan, 18; Ding
Shanyang, 21; and Zhang Eryang, 20; who are all from Shuyang
County, Jiangsu, 250 km north of the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
According to previous reports, at midnight on April 1, the four
broke into the Nanjing residence of the Pfrang family, including
Jurgen Hermann Pfrang, 50, and his 40-year-old wife, Petra Pfrang,
and their two children, daughter Sandra Melanie Pfrang, 15, and
Thorsten Oliver Pfrang, 13.
</P>
<P>
All the four members of the Pfrang family were fatally stabbed
by the criminals who were caught on the spot by guards patrolling
the residential block and confessed all their criminal activities
to the police.
</P>
<P>
The case, involving "extremely fierce means" of slaughtering,
is "particularly execrable" and has resulted in "extraordinarily
severe consequences", and it poses enormous threat to the society,
says the court verdict.
</P>
<P>
Some 300 people attended an open trial on the case held from
May 19-20 and today's sentencing.
</P>
<P>
Jurgen Hermann Pfrang was deputy general manager of Yaxing Benz
Ltd., a Sino-German joint venture bus manufacturer based in
Yangzhou City, Jiangsu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
