<HEADLINE> Six Killed in Fresh Clash in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- At least six people were killed
and 12 others injured in fresh clash in Ambon, capital of
Indonesia's Maluku province, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Most of the victims seemed to have been hit by bullets from
security forces as well as from rioters, according to reports
reaching here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The latest clashes erupted after a gunfight occurred between
speedboats off Teluk Ambon Baguala on Thursday morning. News of
the gunfight spread quickly and provoked armed aggressors to take
to the streets.
</P>
<P>
Rioters destroyed at least four houses with bombs and grenades
in the ensuing violence.
</P>
<P>
Security forces appeared unable to prevent the destruction, and
explosions and gunfire were still heard in the city as of late
Thursday evening, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Maluku Governor Saleh Latuconsina refused to comment on this
latest outbreak of violence, but warned that provocateurs were
trying to spread more terror outside the city.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very concerned about this violence and it is up to the
security forces to handle it," he was quoted by the Jakarta Post
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Sporadic clashes have continued despite the state of emergency
imposed last month in the Maluku and North Maluku provinces, where
18-month fighting between Muslims and Christians has claimed more
than 3,000 lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
