<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan's Mt. Oyama Erupts Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Mt. Oyama on Miyakejima, a small
volcanic island some 180 kilometers south of Tokyo, erupted again
early Friday, the Kyodo news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The eruption occurred at around 4.14 a.m. (1914 GMT Thursday),
shortly after the island's meteorological observatory confirmed a
column of smoke rising 1,000 meters above the mountain top, Kyodo
quoted the Meteorological Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
Pale gray ashes were flowing in a northeasterly direction while
a thunder-like sound was heard from the mountain's summit around 5.
24 a.m. (2024 GMT Thursday), said the agency.
</P>
<P>
The agency has decided not to issue evacuation orders for local
residents as it does not think a major eruption is imminent,
agency officials were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time Mt. Oyama has erupted in a week
following an eruption last Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
