<HEADLINE> Flexible Residence Registration Policy Introduced to help Develop West </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Investors and professionals
working in the western parts of China will have more choices in
deciding their families' permanent residence status.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Public Security recently issued a notice,
stipulating that all working in west China can leave their
permanent residence registrations as they are, or can have them
registered where they work. And if they return to where they came
from, they can have their residence registration go with them.
</P>
<P>
The new policy is aimed at providing a better environment for
the country to carry out its west development strategy and
encouraging a reasonable and orderly population immigration.
</P>
<P>
The notice also encourages the household registration reform in
small cities and towns. It stipulates that farmers can apply for
urban residence registration in cities at the county level and
towns unless they have stable jobs and income there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
