<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CITIC Industrial Bank Offers New Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua)-- The CITIC Industrial Bank, one of
China's rising commercial banks, announced Thursday the debut of
its on-line banking services and credit card, which marked an
upgrade of its traditional businesses.
</P>
<P>
The newly-issued CITIC credit card is believed to be a real one
that fits in with international practice, today's China Daily
reported.
</P>
<P>
Holders of the card can spend before they deposit the money
into their account. They are allowed to withdraw as much as 50,000
yuan (6.025 U.S. dollars) at one time and repay the money in 45
days without paying interest.
</P>
<P>
Although a new commercial bank operating in tune with
international standards and free from the burden of large amounts
of non-performing loans as in State-owned commercial banks, CITIC
said it was "old" in terms of financial product.
</P>
<P>
"All CITIC bank's financial products were traditional and could
not meet the demand of the rapidly developing new economy," said
Wang Jun, CITIC Group board director in an earlier conference.
</P>
<P>
Realizing the impetus brought by Internet on the traditional
banking services, CITIC is actively upgrading its products,
according to Dou Jianzhong, president of the bank.
</P>
<P>
The bank is the first to adopt the certificates of the newly
founded China Financial Certificate Authorization Center (CFCA) to
guarantee the safety of on-line banking, said CFCA General Manager
Liu Dalong.
</P>
<P>
The CFCA was founded by the central bank and 12 major
commercial banks last month, which grants CA certificates to e-
commerce users on the basis of careful credit record inspection.
</P>
<P>
The on-line banking business of Chinese banks have stepped into
actual operational stage, and "Chinese and foreign banks are quite
on the same level in the development of on-line banking," said
Chen Jing, an official with the central bank's payment technology
department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
