<HEADLINE> Colombian Army Troops Seize Over One Tone of Cocaine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A cargo of 1,259 kilos of cocaine
was seized by army troops in the department of Boyaca in the
center of the country during an operation in which a drug
trafficker died and five more were captured.
</P>
<P>
Military authorities briefed reporters Friday of the seizure of
10,000 dollars in cash, emeralds, diamonds and gold jewelry, which
according to General Fabio Bedoya, the commander of the army unit
that made the confiscation, has a value of more than 300 billion
pesos ( some 236,000 dollars).
</P>
<P>
General Bedoya said that the drug and the valuables were
transported in two pickup trucks, a dump truck and a public
service autobus.
</P>
<P>
An unidentified man died during the combat between the troops
and the drug traffickers, and five more were detained.
</P>
<P>
The army officer said that the destination of the cargo has not
been determined yet, but that it can be supposed that it was
Bogota, the capital of the country, according to the direction the
motorcade was following. The value of the drug was estimated by
Bedoya at 30 million or 40 million dollars. 
</P>
