<HEADLINE> Spain to Cancel Nigeria's Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Spain has agreed to write off the 1.
6 billion naira (16 million U. S. dollars) that Nigeria owes to
it, visiting Spanish Foreign Affairs Minister of State Mogul Nadal
has said.
</P>
<P>
Modalities for the cancellation will be worked out before
Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo's visit to Spain next month,
Nigerian press said here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
At another round of talks on Friday with his Nigerian
counterpart Dubem Onyia, the spanish minister said debt
repudiation needed a global approach, for "Spain is only a
marginal player since Nigeria is not owing us so much".
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that the volume of trade between the two countries
hit 1 billion U.S. dollars last year, and Spanish businessmen have
strong interest in investing in Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Span is the second industrialized country after Canada to offer
to cancel Nigeria's debt. Nigeria, with its external debt of some
30 billion dollars, is Africa's most indebted country. 
</P>
