<HEADLINE> China to Send New Medical Team to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China will send a new medical
team, the 11th of its kind since 1980, to render its services in
Ethiopia on the eve of the 30th anniversary of the establishment
of diplomatic ties between the two countries, according to an
agreement signed between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Ethiopia Jiang Zhengyun and Ethiopian
Vice Minister of Economic Development and Cooperation Mulatu
Teshome signed the agreement on behalf of their respective
governments here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the signing ceremony, Mulatu spoke highly of
friendly cooperation between Ethiopia and China, saying that the
latest agreement would further the bilateral friendly relationship.
</P>
<P>
In response, Jiang said that it has been over 20 years since
the first Chinese medical team was sent to Ethiopia by the Chinese
government.
</P>
<P>
The practice of dispatching medical team has turned out to be
one of helpful and effective ways of cooperation in the field of
health between China and African countries, including Ethiopia, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The 15-member Chinese medical team, due to arrive here in
August, is expected to provide its services in Nazareth, about 100
kilometers south of Addis Ababa, and a dental center affiliated to
Addis Ababa University.
</P>
<P>
China and Ethiopia established diplomatic ties on November 24,
1970. 
</P>
</TEXT>
