<HEADLINE> 1 Million Ugandans Displaced  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 1 million people have been
displaced from their homes because of the rebel activities in
northern and western Uganda, the New Vision daily reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of people have recently been displaced by rebels of
the Lords Resistance Army (LRA) in the north and Allied Defence
Forces (ADF) in the west, according to a report by the Disaster
Preparedness Division in the Office of the Prime Minister.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 832,493 people were displaced countrywide during
1999-2000 financial year, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Gulu, a north district of Uganda, has the highest number of
people forced to leave their home, amounting to 308,760, which is
closely followed by Kitgum, another north district of Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The rebel LRA and ADF fighting against the Ugandan government
are based in the southern Sudan and the east Democratic Republic
of the Congo respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
