<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's 21 districts bordering
the Democratic Republic of the Congo and the Sudan are to undergo
a mass polio immunization program, Manager of Uganda National
Expanded Immunization Program Issa Makumbi said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Over 1 million children are being targeted to receive a dose
of polio vaccine," Makumbi told Xinhua in a telephone interview,
adding the children between 6 months and 5 years old are to
receive a supplementation of vitamin A.
</P>
<P>
The program will take place during the first Sub-National
Immunization Days in late August and early September, said Makumbi.
</P>
<P>
The program is aimed at polio eradication in the east Africa
country, he said, adding that mass polio immunization program will
continue in the future. 
