<HEADLINE> London Stock Market Ends Little Changed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The London stock market was little
changed Friday with drug companies on the decline and technology
and telecom stocks powering higher.
</P>
<P>
Its blue-chip FTSE 100 index ended 0.3 points lower at 6,475.4
points with gainers narrowly outnumbering losers five to four.
</P>
<P>
Volumes were a relatively robust 1.5 billion shares, boosted by
turnover of 125 million shares in market debutante Carphone
Warehouse.
</P>
<P>
Drug maker SmithKline Beecham dropped 4.7 percent and its
merger partner Glaxo Wellcome lost 4.7 percent. AstraZeneca
slipped 2 percent and biotech-firm Celltech dropped 2.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Tech shares were the best performers on FTSE index. Sema Group
jumped 7.6 percent, CMG was up 9.2 percent, and IT consulting firm
Misys added 7.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The UK's telecom sector also was strong, with Colt Telecm
rising 8.1 percent, rival British Telecom adding 1.2 percent, and
Internet data carrier Energis climbing 4.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE Eurotop 300 index, a basket of Europe's largest
companies, rose 0.1 percent, with its insurance segment up 2.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
Frankfurt's Xetra Dax jumped 122.05 points. or 1.7 percent, to
7,318.04, with reinsurer Munich Re up 7.6 percent and insurer
Allianz adding 7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Paris stock market was closed for the Bastille Day holiday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
