<HEADLINE> Seven Colombian Marines Drown in Inirida River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Seven Colombian Marine soldiers
died Friday when the fast boat they were moving with other 14
persons along the Inirida River in the eastern department of
Guainia capsized, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The mishap occurred in a section of the river close to Puerto
Inirida, capital of the Guainia department in the region of the
border with Venezuela, some 800 kilometers southeast of Bogota.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of the victims were found by Civil Defense and Fire
Department volunteers, while the other 14 passengers of the fast
boat could reach the banks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
